				\begin{document}$$y = {\mathrm{cI}} + ({\mathrm{cF}} - {\mathrm{cI}})/\left( {x^n/(k^n + x^n)} \right.$$\end{document}y=cI+(cF−cI)/xn/(kn+xn)where y is the percentage of cleaved DNA, cI is the initial cleavage, cF is the final cleavage, k is the CC50 (the concentration of inhibitor that results in cleavage of 50% of DNA), n is a slope factor and x is the inhibitor concentration.
